dismissalComment.html: taken by slip! At long last, Ireland have managed to get a hand on one of his mis-hits. Length on middle stump, turning away. Looks for the slog sweep and gets a top edge that climbs feebly for the slip fielder to run behind and hold on

dismissalText.commentary: Rahmat Shah b Dockrell 54 (66b 8x4 0x6) SR: 81.81

dismissalComment.html: through him and that's a wicket they desperately needed! tossed up on a length, he just pushed down the wrong line and it burst through the gap between bat and pad to hit middle

commentTextItems.html: short on middle and he has hammered that over the deep midwicket fence

commentPostTextItems.html: 7.50pm Bad news folks, the match has been called off, which means Afghanistan still lead the five match series one-nil. Thanks for joining us.
6.20pm We see no visuals of the scheduled inspection
6.00pm Afghanistan innings is complete. Umpires will inspect at 6.15 (12.45 GMT) and hoping to start at 6.30
The groundsmen are bringing the covers on. A drizzle that started few minutes ago has got heavier and the umpires have taken the players off the field

commentTextItems.html: yorker outside off, squeezed away to short third-man
length on the pads, tucked away to fine-leg
fired in on middle, pushed to long-on

commentTextItems.html: attempted reverse sweep, struck on the thigh pad
length on middle, pushed to cover
full outside off, squeezed to point
fired in on middle, down the wicket and pushes it to long-on

slower ball on off, makes room and pushes it to point for a quick single

length on middle, whipped away to deep squareleg
big appeal for lbw but probably sliding down!
